com.mapbox.services.android.navigation.ui.v5.voice

Interface SpeechPlayer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NavigationSpeechPlayer

    public interface SpeechPlayer
    Defines a contract for speech players used in NavigationView.
    Since:
    0.6.0

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • play

        void play(SpeechAnnouncement speechAnnouncement)
        Will play the given string speechAnnouncement. If a voice speechAnnouncement is already playing or other speechAnnouncement are already queued, the given speechAnnouncement will be queued to play after.
        Parameters:
        speechAnnouncement - with voice speechAnnouncement data.
        Since:
        0.15.1

      • isMuted

        boolean isMuted()
        Returns:
        true if currently muted, false if not
        Since:
        0.6.0

      • setMuted

        void setMuted(boolean isMuted)
        Will determine if voice announcements will be played or not.

        If called while an announcement is currently playing, the announcement should end immediately and any announcements queued should be cleared.

        Parameters:
        isMuted - true if should be muted, false if should not
        Since:
        0.6.0

      • onOffRoute

        void onOffRoute()
        Used in off-route scenarios to stop current announcement (if playing) and voice a rerouting cue.
        Since:
        0.6.0

      • onDestroy

        void onDestroy()
        Used to stop and release the media (if needed).
        Since:
        0.6.0
